CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 20, 1958, pg. 21 reads: "Await Kickoff - Members of the Cyclone A.C. football team are scheduled to open the football season at Kennard Field, Friday, at 8:15 P.M., against the Greenfield Preps. Squad members are Douglas Lane, Lenny Picardi, Melvin Jackson, Patrick Kelly, Ronald Gray, Ricky Benjamin, Nicky Philistine, Melvin Lane, George Sapps, Fred Green, Ralph Campbell, William Jones, Pete Brenna, Louis Allen, Don Sauro and Earl Johnson.  The youngsters, all of whom hail from Terrace Village, have been able to supply themselves with all the necessary equipment except football pants.  They are hoping that interested citizens in community will help them obtain the pants. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Cyclone A. C. football team, including Douglas Lane, Lenny Picardi, Melvin Jackson, Patrick Kelly, Ronald Gray, Ricky Benjamin, Nicky Philistine, Melvin Lane, George Sapps, Fred Green, Ralph Campbell, William Jones, Pete Brenna, Louis Allen, Don Sauro, and Earl Johnson, posed on Kennard Field
